name: Boulevard Restaurant

reviews.text:
The food was simple and classic and boy is it tasty. My fish was perfectly cooked and my plate was basically licked clean.

The interior decor reminds me somewhat of a wine cellar that was turned into an elegant home. The bricks on the ceiling and airy feel from the wall of windows looking out into the streets of San Francisco make it urban enough to enjoy a "night out on the town".

The attire is business casual although, I don't believe they'll turn anyone away. This is San Francisco after all. Valet is right outside for those hard-to-find parking spots so no need to plan for extra parking time. This restaurant is truly a gem within a city on the bay.

We dined in their cellar room. Had to make a reservation months in advance. Very nice space for a group of ten to twelve guests. A few minor interuptions as this is the restaurant's cellar where they retrieve the wines for guests .  All food ordered was delicious and cooked as ordered. The steak was tender and cooked to perfection. Crab salad was very good as well. Everyone in our party was pleased with their food, cocktails and wine.

Boulevard creates the most beautiful and flavorful dishes I've ever tasted. For those who know what TBO refers to, this is the place. Amazing wine list and plenty of non-alcoholic refreshing drinks. Service impeccable. Price...who cares?
Came here for presentation. Very good food. Amazing service. I had sea bass and cheesecake. Probably one of best I’ve had.
Delicious food, woody & warm decor (a little masculine in a nice way. Great service. A bit pricey, but not over-priced.

adr_address: 730 Larkin St, San Francisco, CA 94109-7117, USA
formatted_address: 730 Larkin St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
name: Lers Ros

reviews.text: This place has very fresh Thai Food. The staff is great and very helpful if you have questions on what to try. A bunch of us came and ended up sharing many of the meals on each other's plates and they were all very good. I had the pad Thai with chicken and it's up there with some of the best I've ever had.
Best Thai i have ever had hands down. This place is always busy and my Thai friends recommend it highly. Dont leave without trying the green papaya salad.

Great food at ler ros. Got the vegetarian options - the red curry and the pad see yew. Both were really good and had enough to take home after. 
Not the best Thai spot in the city, but would go again if in the area.

This place has proven multiple times to be unable to deliver on time. If you use Caviar or another food delivery app, know that your food will arrive over 45 minutes later than expected. Unacceptable.

The two blocks stretch between O'Farrell and Eddie has six Thai restaurants to choose from so I decided to start with Lers Ros as it had 4 stars rating with over 2000 reviews. On a Friday evening it was packed to the brim with people waiting outside for a table. I was hesitant to get something but as I simply wanted something to-go I walked in and ordered.

I decided to get the Kuay Tiew Rua ($11.95) which is just a fancy name for Thai Boat Noodle soup. After ordering I paid and then proceeded to wait outside. I waited and waited and then waited some more. Without exaggeration I waited about 40 minutes in the cold for a simple order of boat noodle soup. Each time I asked about the progress I was told it was it was almost done. Finally, when I asked for the order to be cancelled they gave me the soup. 

I good news is that I got 2 containers one with the noodles and the other with the broth which keeps the noodles from becoming soggy. The bad news is that the broth lacked seasoning. It had a ton of spices as I had asked for spicy but they seemed to be simply added to the broth rather than being properly cooked with it. Another issue was that the quantity of noodles in the order was very little and were all clumped together. Goes without saying I did not like what I got. 

Price-wise this was about 20% more than the same dish in Pak Nam Thai noodle bar and 10% less than Lapats Thai Noodle Bar both of which are just a block down the road. Unfortunately, the quality is nowhere even close to what you can get at the other two places. I had high hopes for Lers Ros given its high ratings but I was thoroughly disappointed with my visit. With so many options in its vicinity I doubt that I will return.

adr_address: 1652 Stockton St, San Francisco, CA 94133-3316, USA
formatted_address: 1652 Stockton St, San Francisco, CA 94133, USA
name: Park Tavern

reviews.text: Upscale dining can be impersonal. Not here. We had a large party and we were treated warmly and the service never skipped a beat. Atmosphere was inviting as opposed to stuffy and pretentious. Food was yummy and we were eager to sample each others. The balance of good food, atmosphere and service was very much appreciated.

One of my favorites - love the atmosphere, attentive staff, and delicious food and drinks. Was there for the Super Bowl and had the BEST time. Eat the meatball, it's ridiculously good! Thanks especially to the manager for finding a seat for us when it was so packed! Will definitely be back!

Really great upscale restaurant that's perfect for business or personal occasions. I met a friend here for dinner and liked how dark the place is yet very cool and sophisticated. The drinks were great as was my meal. I'd definitely come back in the future!

Awesome place for an upscale dinner in a casual environment. It can get packed but the bar area rotates pretty quickly and they also have a communal table. The Spanish Octopus for dinner was incredible, big meaty tentacles full of flavor and great presentation. For starters, if you love lemons then the lemon chips are a must-try, served with burrata and fresh Italian parsley. Lots of wood and soft lighting contribute to its rustic tavern feel.

I only had a drink here, but they did have a few selections of craft brews I haven't seen anywhere else. Sat at the bar and the staff was friendly. They were packed mid afternoon on a Sunday. Prices in the menu looked to be on the higher side. Looking around at others plates, the food did look really good...again, I can't speak for the food itself.

adr_address: 865 Market St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
formatted_address: 865 Market St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Westfield San Francisco Centre

reviews.text: The Westfield Mall gets 5 stars for the following reasons. The size of the mall is very impressive and I really like going to the top floor there you are underneath this dome which is beautiful. Next, I like for the most part the different stores they provide. This is important that the Westfield Mall keeps this course as I see more stores outside of the mall closed. Last, the food to choose from. I love it no I hate it no I love having the option of choosing my dish to eat from a ton of different places in the food court. The Westfield Mall in San Francisco gets 5 stars and  everyone should come out and support this business.

Westfield is a standard US mega mall with 4 floors, a myriad of mid to high-end shops and a massive food court on the lowest level. They are some unique restaurants on the upper floor and a movie theater at the top. The lower level includes a high-end grocery store with many organic and international products as well as a bakery. The lower level also gives direct access to the Metro. And if you need to exchange money their is a money exchange also.

Fun people watching.  Plenty of entertainment.  However, not so much parking.  Hard to find a free spot, nearly impossible.  There are lots and garages that charge by the hour.  Friendly folks, lots of awesome shopping and food, and always something new to do or discover.  San Francisco is always a good time.  Great to visit but expensive to live there, although there minimum wage is higher than most areas, if not the highest.  Can never go wrong with a visit to the city.  Smell that ocean air!

A historic building with an impressive gate. Mens store at top floor has many great brands and most of the time offer great deals and discounts. Not too crowded upstairs but can sometimes be overwhelming downstairs. Very nice ceiling decor at the restaurant floor upstairs.

The Westfield San Francisco Centre is beautiful!  We  enjoyed walking around each floor even though we didn’t buy anything. BART, Buses, Cable cars all have stops right outside.  We walked from our hotel.

adr_address: 673 Union St, San Francisco, CA 94133, USA
formatted_address: 673 Union St, San Francisco, CA 94133, USA
name: Rogue Ales Public House

reviews.text: Best bar in San Francisco! My wife and I just walked a little bit around the city to find a spot to chill and eat when we came across Rogue. All-around great service and fantastic selections - especially for the ones who like imperial stouts! Their 2017 Rolling Thunder Imperial Stout is fantastic and the food there was perfect bar food. All the food we had chicken tenders + fries, cheese curds, and soft pretzel sticks were world-class. Great service and they are a fantastic value for the price! If you plan on going to a bar, GO THERE! You won't regret it!

Tons of beer options!  They had a bunch of their own stuff and like 10 or so guest taps too.  They also had nearly everything bottled, or you could always get a growler too.  I ended up trying 8 or so of their beers, and the standouts for me were the Fresh Roast Brown, and the Chocolate Stout.  The other beers were also good though.  I didn't try any food, but what I saw looked good.  The bartender was great though.  He was a man who liked beer and had no problem giving you his real opinion on the beer options.  He talked us off a couple of beers and in to a few others.  And the recommendations from him that we tried definitely worked out in our favor.

Closed due a large fire.
It was an excellent bar in great location with a wide range of beers. We dropped I'm here while visiting Washington Square and as it was only just approaching lunchtime there was only a few in here. The bar man was friendly and as we are not from this country he recommended some beers to try. Unfortunately we didn't have time to try the food.

Went out with some friends. We couldn't get into some clubs. Frustrating night, getting late. drove by this place and stopped by. This place change the energy of the party. Great beers, great service, good company. We ended up drunk and laughing about the unfortunate events. Thank you Rogue for saving the night.
Great vibe in the place. Had great beer and some yummy cheese curds. Good place to hang out with friends.

adr_address: 620 Treat Ave, San Francisco, CA 94110-2016, USA
formatted_address: 620 Treat Ave, San Francisco, CA 94110, USA
name: Southern Pacific Brewing

reviews.text: This place is the inner mission is a hidden gem and really well tucked away. The beer selection is on point and the bar food is also quite good. The old converter warehouse is fantastic and has a very industrial feel to it with its giant propeller fans. That’s if you don’t want to sit outside in their beer garden and enjoy an Sf summer .

Really cool venue and neat hang out spot, for sure. It gets a bit crazy on weekend afternoons and evenings, so get ready to fight for a table or you'll have to stand around. 

- Outdoor and indoor seating. Feel free to bring the pup if you're hanging outside! 
- Food is really good! Mac and cheese, fries, burger are things I've tried and they are all good.
- Decent selection of beers and cocktails.

Their house beers are solid but nothing ground breaking. They always have a few good guest taps. I did not eat there this time but I have before. Their food is pretty good for SF. Mostly typical pub food done well. Limited menu. This place is big but can get pretty slammed on weekends. Good spot for day drinking.

I had been here before, but I won't come again for some time, if ever. The tall, attractive bartender with curly hair was amazingly rude to us regarding several things. There seemed to be no reason to be so confrontational, but this person was beyond brisk. We came in for a beer before going to dinner and were greeted poorly, and it only got worse from there. We're a pretty chill group of nerds, so I didn't and don't understand why we were treated as we were.  Won't walk out of the way to get to this place again with my teams.

The warehouse turned bar is a chill place to hang out in the Mission, particularly if you're getting off from a climb at Mission Cliffs. There's plenty of space spread across two floors and an outdoor patio. I love how they've placed trees and plants throughout the area. They have a good beer collection. And their for options are quite good as well.

adr_address: 230 California St, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
formatted_address: 230 California St, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
name: Perbacco

reviews.text: Great menu with large selection of dishes. Appreciated the available option of ordering half portion of pasta in order to leave room for a main meat dish. Excellent wine selection, from affordable wines sold in small carafes to more costly, exquisite wines. Service staff is very friendly and knowledgeable. I first visited Perbacco in 2007 and have been back several times since then. It continues to impress.
Very nice Italian restaurant.  I loved the apple-pear salad.  Others in my party were pleased with their entrees.  I ordered the duck breast which was a bit dry, but it did have good flavor.
Once a year they do an Italian inspired Passover Seder using Joyce Goldsteins recipies. Joyce is there. In general, excellent food and service.
The food was amazing, everything was perfectly prepared.  We we're in the upstairs dining room and it was a very nice and relaxing environment.

Every dish I've ever had here has been cooked perfectly. They have all had great flavor. The portions are a little small, but that leaves room for an appetizer or dessert. The servers are very attentive as well.

adr_address: 347 Geary St, San Francisco, CA 94102-1801, USA
formatted_address: 347 Geary St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
name: Daily Grill

reviews.text: I loved the menu. I got the chicken pot pie and it was very good. I am not sure if someone called out because they were a tad understaffed but our waiter was exceptional. The tater tots that were the appetizer special were very good. Good prices as well.

The breakfast here is delicious and the portion sizes ridiculously large. The staff are friendly, courteous and very helpful. The atmosphere in the restaurant is nice. It was busy but quiet. Would definitely eat here again.

This place has a nice ambiance, ample seating, friendly staff, and tasty food (based on what we had ... Reuben sandwich and chicken pot pie). A star lost due to the wait for our order. But, generally speaking, it was a good experience, worth going back to.

We ordered two burgers from the chef's special lunch menu. The flavour was amazing and I was impressed by the quality although it was supposed to be spicy and it wasn't so that let me down a bit. 

The service was good, courteous but not friendly. The place was almost empty and quite gloomy but casual. The prices were ok but considering it's in the center of SF, it's cheap-ish/comfortable. 

Food 4.5/5
Price 4/5
Place 4/5
Service 4/5

Our dinner was cooked perfectly and the service was excellent. We told them that we like to eat slowly and have some time between the courses. Of course, we only do this when the restaurant is not (!) jammed. They asked us when they should fire each course and that worked perfectly.

adr_address: 2929, 582 Washington St, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
formatted_address: 2929, 582 Washington St, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
name: Taverna Aventine

reviews.text: Awful food, bartender for a private event was rude..small seating for 5 people.nobody to pick up dirty dishes. Served cheese (old)with salami and no crackersI left early and would never have a event there. Bummer since that is what I do..oh well..
Good place for drinks and finger food!

Great place. Convenient location.

Tuesday - free appetizers

Great happy hour and one of the only ones in the financial district that goes past 6pm. $8 glasses of good wine and lots of small bite options. Cheese board is not on happy hour menu but is substantial and delicious!
Amazing food, great location, good prices and fun atmosphere!

adr_address: 741 Valencia St, San Francisco, CA 94110, USA
formatted_address: 741 Valencia St, San Francisco, CA 94110, USA
name: Tacolicious

reviews.text: Cool spot for tacos. Fun vibes. If you're in a tequila mood, definitely swing by here. Their margaritas are on point & strong! We sat outside bc indoor seating was too packed. They give you blankets if its chilly.

Got seated quickly as we were only two people and this was around 7pm.  The tacos were very good but the pork belly was a bit much belly than pork... Almost all fat... I really didn't enjoy it. The rest were good.
Tacos were average for the price. Chips and salsa was nice as well as the margaritas. The Children’s cheese quesadilla wasn’t very crisp and they weren’t eaten.
Very large tacos, at least twice the size than at other taquerias. The fish ones are great, so are the vegetable ones that change seasonally. Fun drinks and mescal next door at Mosto.
Delicious! The service was excellent and the food  was incredible. Has a bustling atmosphere in a great location.

adr_address: 200 Larkin St, San Francisco, CA 94102-4734, USA
formatted_address: 200 Larkin St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
name: Cafe Asia

reviews.text: Pleasant cafe inside the Asian Art Museum. It’s a great place to have a light lunch and to enjoy  tea in between visits to different parts of the museum.

Surprisingly good food and value for a museum cafe.  Dim sum basket was 8 pieces for 8.5$.  Lentil soup was great comfort food.  Thai iced tea and blackberry lemonade completed the meal.  Veg noodles and pork dishes available.

For museum food, it's more than acceptable! Sure, I'd rather eat in one of the cheaper restaurants outside, but sometimes I'm just one big ball of lazy. If I'm already in the museum, I won't venture out. Lunchtime seems to be the peak when all the tables inside appear full, and the line is long and bustling. Surprisingly, by the time you get through the line, there are tables ready. On a sunny day, there's outdoor seating that one should also take advantage of. 

The food can be a little on the luke warm side because everything is prepared already. They just throw it together when you place the order. It saves them time, and you don't have to wait too long for your food. Everything is served in the most adorable dishes. Condiments available include Thai chili sauce and Sriracha! YUM!
Very very rude service!
Nice cafe in the museum

adr_address: 685 4th St, San Francisco, CA 94107-1601, USA
formatted_address: 685 4th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
name: The Creamery

reviews.text:
This is a decent coffee shop with good coffee, it can take a while to be served though even when empty.

 When I last visited I was one of five people there and was ignored by the person who was working front of house and ended up being served by someone who noticed me standing at the counter from where they were working in the kitchen. The gentleman that served me was great though.

If you have plenty of time and want to watch the world go by (or just listen to the various pitches going on all around you) then you can do a lot worse in San Francisco.
Close to the station. And pickles lox and cream cheese. Suited my needs.

Stopped by this location for quick bite before heading back to Los Angeles. Service was fast, food was of good quality, and the atmosphere gave me a cosy feeling. The chef served up a great breakfast sandwich, one if the best I've had in a while. No complaints!
Good for snacks, beer, wine and coffee.  They have cocktails but it's not a core strength.

Friendly staff, promptly prepared and tasty breakfast.  The establishment has been in the same spot for eight years...I would take occasional coffee breaks there while at a  long ago job nearby. Such longevity for cafe speaks volumes.

adr_address: 3176 17th St, San Francisco, CA 94110, USA
formatted_address: 3176 17th St, San Francisco, CA 94110, USA
name: Mission Bowling Club

reviews.text: This place was really cool. It's a bowling alley with a scratch kitchen and craft bar. The Mac and cheese is really good. If you want a good drink done right, hit up the bartender by the name of Sean, he will up you with something that will get you right for the night. This is a very cool spot to hang out with friends on a Friday night in the Mission District.
Really cool vibes, amazing amazing staff! Alyssa (sp?) was incredible. Perfect place for a good time.

I had a very difficult experience than most people. I ordered a medium Mission burger, but the burger was severely undercooked-almost raw. When I told my waiter, Mitch, about my burger he said, "what do you want me to do about it?" I asked for a different meal- the fried chicken appetizer. The chicken was also undercooked, but I chose not to say anything. Once I got my check, I saw the server literally watching me sign it from afar. That was the first time I never left a tip. I understand that the food was not his fault, but his attitude and lack of apology was what did it. I was really disappointed as I had been anticipating going to this place for months. Hopefully you will have a better experience.
Their hamburger is really good although a tad pricey. Thick, succulent, tasty. So is the not-too-sweet scone with nuts I had for dessert good for the palate.

Ok. Big Lebowski. Netflix much? Well, you should. Let me tell you, this little cinema gem turned me onto what I believe to be the most happening neighborhood local-friendly pin tavern that takes the idea of classic vintage activity and nails it with a strike.

Well - the gripe. The lanes are, well, as available as limited edition elderflower kombucha at 12pm in the Gus's bev aisle. Don't plan on reserving a startup funding party here, and throw the idea of walk-in right down the gutter.

Nachos: 6.5/10
Service: 8/10
Ambiance: 9/10

What they DO have are the low style urinals, various ball weights / hole tightnesses, and my (quite frankly) stunning fiance rolled a 100+ game utterly decimating my sub par performance as usual. Let's just say SHE had a good time, and I did too if the nachos count as a perfect game.

Cons: Dirty disgusting gas station at the corner, hooligans in what appears to be a hotel across the street, and what seems to be run-down cafes and restaurants encompassing the radius of this booming establishment.

If you can even make it in here on a busy night, get ready for good food, good atmosphere and GOOD PEOPLES! -CRK

adr_address: 300 Grove St, San Francisco, CA 94102-4419, USA
formatted_address: 300 Grove St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
name: Jardinière

reviews.text: My husband and I came here to try the impossible burger (which by the way is incredible, it really tastes and feels like real meet). We knew this was somewhat an upscale and expensive restaurant and we were fine with it. The food, service and atmosphere are actually really good. The problem was the bill. We had two martinis before the meal. I had a 209 gin and my husband had a Monkey 47. Now, we know Monkey 47 is more expensive than regular find, but they charged us $43 for a martini. That's what I pay for the entire bottle of Monkey 47 at our local boutique spirit store for a whole bottle. $43 for a martini is obscene and honestly  unacceptable. So, overall this place serves good food, the place is great, but we will never get back and would definitely not recommend.

Friendly staff. Good prices for amazing food.   I had the Charleston Golden Rice - yes as a main dish - and honestly, I didn't know rice could be that good. It was buttery and earthy without being too heavy (is that possible?). My wife had the Wagyu A5 beef - a splurge at $90 for 3 ounces - but oh my god, it was amazing. Along with the apps, salad and soup it was an amazing meal.

I came here for the Impossible Burger when it first came out, and have been coming back ever since for the atmosphere, impeccable (read: OUTSTANDING) service and delicious food. 

My bf and I are both vegan and were stunned at how welcoming and accommodating everyone was about it. We've been back for birthdays, anniversaries etc and always have a delicious meal (not always the Impossible Burger!), amazing wine, and an all-around great time. 

I recently had my 30th birthday here in the private dining room and it was stunning. The vegan menu was delicious, the wine was perfect, the service was above and beyond. Special thank you to Tommie, the event organizer, for helping create such a wonderful night. 

I would recommend this restaurant over and over again.

twas a pretty fantastic first taste of this low-key, yet, utterly sophisticated eatery.. only had pomme fritters and a Hemingway, but the class service and elegant presentation left nothing to be desired. my lady and I visited after mentally taxing 9 to 5s and reinvigorated ourselves on splendid ambiance and meaningful conversation. highly recommended.

I love this place!! Super nice place to eat with amazing food. Its a bit on the fancier/pricey side, but well worth the price they charge. Everything here is super fresh and delicious. They also have an amazing drink/wine menu. For all the vegans, vegetarians or adventurous meat eaters they also offer the impossible burger here... a non meat burger that tastes like meat. Im a vegetarian, and every time im in the city I have to stop here to get this burger... its to die for. The flavor is super delicious and seriously tastes just like meat. Other than that there menu has plenty of seasonal options that will please your pallet

adr_address: 620 Jones St, San Francisco, CA 94102-1643, USA
formatted_address: 620 Jones St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
name: Jones

reviews.text: Nice open outdoor, rooftop feel. The vibe is a grown-ups bar. Good place for small to larger size groups.
Very nice atmosphere on this outdoor patio bar. Just be prepared for 15$ cocktails
Cash only place for SF priced drinks but cool ambient
Nice atmosphere, huge outdoor space for summer. The indoor space is also great with a cool vibe. The crowd age range varies.
Great Location, little hidden from the street. Cocktails are very tasty.

adr_address: 1449, 1090 Point Lobos Ave, San Francisco, CA 94121, USA
formatted_address: 1449, 1090 Point Lobos Ave, San Francisco, CA 94121, USA
name: Cliff House

reviews.text:
If you’re looking for a fine Saturday or Sunday brunch with a splendid view. This is the place!

The pop up bread they serve complimentary is truly amazing! Nice and warm and goes excellent with the jelly served on the table. 

The portions were good size and the Eggs San Francisco were simply amazing a definite must have. 

Excellent location and close to a nice trail if you would like to walk off some calories afterwards.

Had an excellent time there.   Stayed at the lower level bar restaurant and bar.    Prices are high but not astronomic, considering the scenic location.    Bottles of wine were half price with the entree (at the time).     Excellent bartender service at the bar.   View is from the window of the restaurant.   Was overcast but still great experience!

Perfect place for a delicious dinner with a stunning view onto the sea. If the weather is nice and the sky clear, guests can enjoy the beauty of a colourful sunset which appears even more astonishing because of its reflection on the water surface.
The restaurant serves delicious food and drinks for lunch and dinner. The menus often varies according to the season and time of the day.
The staff is very friendly and helpful. They are proud of working at this restaurant and also love to give guests some background information about the local area and its sea.
In closing, the restaurant is definitely worth visiting during a stay in San Francisco.

While waiting over an hour to be seated, we watched dogs frolic on the beach, birds wafting in the sea breeze and marveled at the sheer size of container ships passing by. Visiting from the desert, the view is the main attraction. Inside, there is little seating for those waiting to be served. However, our table provided a panoramic view of the water and the wait was quickly forgotten. Our server was friendly, attentive and we recognized his service with generous tip. The breakfast items we ordered were made better with the generous helpings of Dungeness crab. 
Overall, tourists looking for a decent meal with a one-of-a-kind, memorable view, need look no further than the iconic Cliff House. Bravo!

The food was very good, I had the Caesar salad and clam chowder.   For me, It's funny to go to a restaurant just to order the Caesar, but that's what I wanted that day. . . it was very well prepared and delicious.  Everything we ate tasted fresh.   Added to my list of restaurants to revisit!

adr_address: 510 Embarcadero West, Oakland, CA 94607, USA
formatted_address: 510 Embarcadero West, Oakland, CA 94607, USA
name: Yoshi's Oakland

reviews.text: Love the Oakland site better than the SF. It is more intimate and there’s nothing like hearing the train go by during the performances. If you don’t feel up for sushi, you can get your hand stamped and dine elsewhere beforehand. Parking gets validated. It is my favorite jazz venue—so intimate. There really isn’t a bad seat in the house. Highly recommend!

I am extremely grateful that we have Yoshi's here in the East Bay.  She runs the very Best Jazz Club and gets such a variety of acts.
From Goapele to Tower of Power & from Nancy Wilson to Sergio Mendes, you KNOW are going to have the best time you have had in a cool minute.
Let's give a shout out to their Awesome staff who obviously work super hard and have the sweetest gig.
Great jazz club. Recently they have done some much-needed improvement. It’s my go to venue for great music.
Amazing food and the jazz club afterwards was great as well! Larry and his sextet played amazing music for us all night! Service and the interior was good!
Nice spot! J holiday and up being a bit of a comic too

adr_address: 1 Market St, San Francisco, CA 94105-1420, USA
formatted_address: 1 Market St, San Francisco, CA 94105, USA
name: One Market Restaurant

reviews.text: My wife and I have been eating here for years.  The food is always good and the service is usually spot on.  We love the steak and their version of fries. My wife loves the deserts.  They have one that you can pick from 3 or 4 different options so you get a bit of everything. We have even gone in just for desert and drinks.  Love this place!

Always a solid go-to.  The servers here are true professionals.  They have deep knowledge and passion for the food they serve and have an understated elegance about the service.  The location is so great (near the Ferry Building, countless office towers and steps from BART and Muni Underground.)  The food is always great.  This place doesn't get enough love!

Imagine old rich person food, but 3x more expensive.  Not particularly imaginative or exceptional.  It was "okay", but for the price you want more.  Either artistic reach or just plain teeth sinking satisfaction.   It provided neither. - which is not to say that it was a bad experience, just not able to hold up to the restaurants that are really pushing the bar (Or holding the line for comfort)

One Market has been around for years! This was my first visit and I came with high expectations. The restaurant itself is huge. They have a few banquet rooms, and tons of seating. It’s a classic restaurant in how the kitchen area is set up and with the food they serve. 

Service was ok. But I was let down by the food. It was just slightly better than ok. One dish was oddly flavored and lacked complexity. The scallop entree was on the bland side. And my dessert cheesecake was made using gelatin. Overall I felt each dish could have used a bit more attention to detail and execution. 

I will also preface that I have a culinary degree from the CIA in New York.

Good food, but high prices. Very poor vegetarian selection. Though they were willing to customize any dish. Still, it is nice to occasionally see vegetarian options on a menu. Especially in California. Especially in San Francisco.

adr_address: 119 Sacramento St, San Francisco, CA 94111-4001, USA
formatted_address: 119 Sacramento St, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
name: Focaccia Market Bakery

reviews.text: Great breakfast. Went with Jamie and Bruce when jamie ran the marathon. I went to the market street location.
Very good and reasonably priced food and excellent service. If you spend >~8.5$ for breakfast you get free coffee and fruits.
Best salad downtown, lots of awesome choices for toppings (my favorite is when they have caramelized pears).  I'm a pretty big guy and I can hardly finish the large salad. Great and friendly service.

My favorite and freshest salad spot in the financial district. Beware, long lines if you go during the lunch rush. Actually the salad bar always has a line but it moves fast! These workers are awesome and so attentive. I always order my own salad with includes spinach/arugula salad mix, topped with marinated tofu, beets and red peppers or edamame. Sometimes I add in their lemon chicken with light balsamic dressing. Their spicy chicken is also to die for and I occasionally order their mac n cheese from the hot food area. Great lunch spot on the go with fresh, tasty ingredients!
Really good for a sandwich or daily specials. The lines at lunch tend to be long. Try to come at off peak times. The salads are awesome because you can basically make your own and they are huge.

adr_address: 1980 Union St, San Francisco, CA 94123, USA
formatted_address: 1980 Union St, San Francisco, CA 94123, USA
name: Extreme Pizza

reviews.text: Ordered a sandwich, came out wrong, mentioned it was wrong, they said they would correct it, came out wrong again. Decided to eat it anyway because.....why wait over 15 minutes for a sub to be made correct on a 30 min lunch break?
Careful, this place is filthy - inside and out.
Delicious pizza the salads look really tasty
Answer the phone!! It’s a pizza joint! Answer your phone!
Best Gluten-Free crust ever! Kinda on the pricey side but it's the biggest GF pizza you'll ever get! The quality of it is fantastic too. Love this pizza joint!

adr_address: 2020 Shattuck Ave, Berkeley, CA 94704, USA
formatted_address: 2020 Shattuck Ave, Berkeley, CA 94704, USA
name: Comal

reviews.text:
You can go to the spaciouss outdoor patio/bar (with fire pits!) while you wait for a table. The cocktails are great, and the food equally so. Excellent design and great service.

Speaking of service: they don't do tips. They simply add a service charge based on the percentage of the meal. This is such a great choice, and I really cannot understate that. The American tipping system is not good for food service workers. I'll gladly support any restaurant that helps fix that system.

Classiest Mexican restaurant in the area. Very vibrant and lots of people. Limited selection on the menu. Just check the door prior to entering to see if you like what they have. Super quick service though, moderately priced drinks and food

Amazing food. Super local, trendy place. Everything on the menu is delicious. I have never been disappointed in any way. Everything from the art on the walls to the stools to the metal work is not only locally done, but suits the restaurant amazingly. Very enjoyable place to eat. They also have a nice bar to sit at if you get there early or if there is a bit of a wait.

Excellent food, a little pricey for what you get - otherwise 5ish stars. Many of the dishes will be familiar (if a bit foodiefied) but if you are more of a novice TALK TO YOUR SERVER and they can help you decide among some of the more unique offerings. Everything we've had here was delicious, double for the salsas. The drinks, both alcoholic and not, are quite good but watch the cost on the cocktails. It isn't unusual to spend $40 per person but if that's cool then you should love the food. If you behave $15-20 pp is doable without drinks. 

The space is lovely and unique with a great back yard and lots more space than you imagine looking in. Always stop, even if it looks crowded.

Beautiful restaurant with an amazing vibe. Tip #1 waiting for a seat? Head to the back patio and enjoy a cocktail until a table opens up. Tip #2 Hungry? Order the larger meat entree and they come with a side. These entrees are perfect for sharing with 2 people and are delicious. Tip #3 thirsty? Order a shot of tequila and it comes with a tasty chaser!

adr_address: 4 Embarcadero Center, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
formatted_address: 4 Embarcadero Center, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
name: Sens

reviews.text: Great outdoor patio with views of the Bay and Ferry building. Wonderful for great weather. The interior decor makes you feel like you are in an old underground cave, great atmosphere all around!  The food is excellent!

Good food and good views! Came here with a big group for lunch. But if you're alone or a small group, you can snag a table by the windows with views of the waterfront. Good place to chill after work or relax after a day of touring SF
Excellent food display at our recent company event. Wine selection was solid. Staff went above and beyond to ensure everyone at the party was happy. Would recommend this place to others!
Great food but a bit pricey, amazing views!
Everyone working here is always super friendly. It's not the most cost effective happy hour location but the variety of drinks and tasty food options keep it in my rotation.

adr_address: 1658 Market St, San Francisco, CA 94102-5949, USA
formatted_address: 1658 Market St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
name: Zuni Café

reviews.text: San Francisco classic that does not disappoint. You might hesitate to get the roast chicken to try something different or flashier but I would say Zuni Cafe is known for their roast chicken for a reason. Because it is so delicious! Also a hearty portion for two. We had quite a bit we took home. Great service as well!

Was here for dinner sometime back. We didn't make a reservation, thankfully someone cancelled his and saved us a long wait. The chicken required an hour to grill upon order. Worth the wait though portion was rather big for 2 people. Zuni salad was average, but the grilled scallop dish was good.

This place steals the show. Every dish is so satisfying and well put together. Great brunch menu, oyster bar, generous selection of wines and apperitifs. Perfect for a catch up with family or friends. Menu highlights are the Zuni salad, the chicken to share, pasta dishes are great for vegetarians, pizzas for sharing and lastly the pavlova is amazing for dessert

Pretty overrated and overpriced. The atmosphere is nice and the service is great and all but the prices don't seem worth it. I guess it depends on how you assign value. That being said the food was good but not spectacular enough for me to want to come back for the price. There are plenty of places in the city with equal to better food for a better price.

A San Francisco staple. The Zuni chicken alone, even with all of its 60min prep time, is worth the trip. Situated directly against Market street, you’ll find Zuni Cafe to be a breath of fresh air surrounded by an “up and coming” area. It’ll take several more years for the neighborhood to catch up but don’t fret, Zuni will be there leading the way. Request a window seat near the kitchen for the people watching, but their upstairs is equally as charming.

adr_address: Pier 5 The Embarcadero, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
formatted_address: Pier 5 The Embarcadero, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
name: Coqueta

reviews.text: It was a very good dinner. We we're the last to be seated on a Sunday night so people we're ready to get out but staff was nice. I would recommend everything but the meatballs. Although they were good they were too sweet for me. Sit at the bar around the kitchen if you can. Very fun to watch the cooks.

Beautiful place for eating and enjoying Spanish small plates and drinks (or a pitcher) with friends. Service is attentive. Restaurant is warm and cozy. Foods can meet the needs of both meat & veg persons. Would recommend to those visiting and those living here.

I have been here twice in the last 4 months. The food and drinks are always good, as is the service. Both times it was hard to get a table, but I was able to sit at the bar. They also change to a limited menu between 3 and 5pm. The sangria is worth trying.

Popular brunch and dinner spot, make sure to get reservations ahead of time. Make sure to try their squid appetizer, and definitely get a paella for the full experience. The cocktail menu is also a crowd favorite.

Food is excellent. Had three tapas and a paella which was plenty for a dinner for two. In fact we didn’t finish the paella. Service was great by the wait staff who do a nice job making recommendations. Definitely get a gin based drink here as they are excellent. Their claaaic gin drink is worth it and extremely tasty.

adr_address: 200 Jackson St, San Francisco, CA 94111-1806, USA
formatted_address: 200 Jackson St, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
name: Kokkari Estiatorio

reviews.text: Every meal I've ever had here has been amazing. The staff are friendly, attentive, and truly care about making every guest feel welcome. I would come here any chance I get for wholesome, delicious, authentic Greek food. Fan for life.

Enjoyed a fabulous dinner for my birthday. The calamari appetizer was amazingly tender and possessed flavors that exploded in your mouth. The lamb chops and the lamb/eggplant casserole-Massuka were wonderfully flavored. The service matched the food, it was way over the top!!

Amazing food. It's a little weird that some tables-for-two are just right next to each other, almost as if it's a four person table. Makes for a suboptimal experience where there's two dates happening at the exact same table. Voices overlap and makes it awkward. Unfortunate floor plan for a great place, with great food and atmosphere.

An absolutely fantastic Greek dining experience. A full bar to start, and wonderful bread. If you can, have the lamb that is roasting on the spit in the center of the front dining room. Delicious. Even better is to be seated at the table in front of the open fire. The fish is magnificent. Make sure to save room for the sundae - decadent.

The staff was warm, friendly and informative. They were able to help us choose apps or salads that would feed just the right amount of people. The food was fabulous. The service was excellent and the ambiance in the room was just perfect. The lighting was not to bright, lots of candles to give it a warm, cozy feeling. Kokarri never lets us down, and is always more than a pleasure to go!!

adr_address: 800 Stanyan St, San Francisco, CA 94117, USA
formatted_address: 800 Stanyan St, San Francisco, CA 94117, USA
name: North Beach Pizza

reviews.text:
I only got a pizza here so I can't judge the rest of the menu.
Pizzas are good, but you should know that if you are looking for a thin crust pizza, like a napolitain style or a new york style pizza, you should keep walking.
Here the pizza have a thick, bread like crust, and a comforting amount of cheese!
I kind of enjoyed it but it's definitely on the heavy side of the pizza world.
Now that you know what kind of pizza to expect, I can say that it's good pizza, crunchy crust, flavorful tomato sauce, nice amount of cheese and a lot of crust to chew on!
The pizza here is amazing! It's a bit expensive but very tasty. It's definitely worth it though.
They use only the cheapest rubbery mozzarella and heap it on their pies. They should be run out of North Beach.
Great service good food

Pizza good enough to eat when in a pinch.

Limited space in restaurant.

adr_address: 4640 Telegraph Ave, Oakland, CA 94609-2022, USA
formatted_address: 4640 Telegraph Ave, Oakland, CA 94609, USA
name: Aunt Mary's Cafe

reviews.text:
Great atmosphere, very kid friendly.  There is a big box of toys that the kids can grab stuff from, and lots of paper and crayons for making pictures. The really good pictures are displayed near the bathroom for those prodigious artistic types.
 All the food seems quite fresh with the possible exception of the pain perdu, which my wife loves but I find that it tastes kind of alcoholic.  
The one downside to the place is that they don't seem to have as much of the traditional California breakfast fare. Everything has a southern twist, which I can never quite get used to. For example the biscuits and gravy is delicious, but they put some sage flavoring in the gravy, which I grew to dislike after the third or fourth time eating it.
Of course the only reason I'm getting tired of some dishes is because we go so often, which in itself is a pretty strong recommendation.

Quaint establishment! Great service very casual. I had the corned beef hash it came with 2 perfectly poached eggs the whites were glistening, white onion and sliced cabbage and a swirl of horseradish sauce! Coffee was great! They had a mini plate with asymmetrical brown sugar cubes for your coffee. I will definitely come back.

Service was amazing and our waitress was on top of our orders from start to finish. I ordered chicken and waffles, hoping that I was going to really enjoy this dish at Aunt Mary’s Cafe. The fried chicken (dry) and waffles were flavorless and the maple syrup that came with the order was not tasty as well. I’ve eaten at Aunt Mary’s Cafe multiple times and have enjoyed all my meals before eating the Chicken and Waffles. Also ordered the pecan pie this morning which was very good👍🏽👍🏽.

Food was great and affordable. Staff was really nice and attentive. I would definitely go again to try other items on the menu. We had an issue with the order and they fixed it immediately and comped our coffees.

Delicious scrambled eggs with Roma tomatoes,  Swiss chard and Asiago cheese accompanied by a large cup of fresh fruit and creamy yellow corn grits.  My husband's eggs came with a wonderful biscuit that he slathered with homemade blueberry preserves. Service was great too. What a find.  Will be back.

adr_address: 1601 Van Ness Ave, San Francisco, CA 94109-3608, USA
formatted_address: 1601 Van Ness Ave, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
name: Ruth's Chris Steak House

reviews.text:
A steak house that serves it's meat in a dish of butter is my kind of steak house.  I've heard rumors about the amount of butter used per steak - some say half a stick, most say a whole stick but I figure you're going there for a gluttonous dinner anyhow. Suck it up and take it as you asked for it.

The steaks are cooked to perfection and if they're not - send it back and request a new one.  After all you are paying for a perfect $45(minimum)+ piece of beef so it should be done right the first time... not the second, or even third.  Ruth's does strive for the perfect temperature, just the way you've asked for it, so hopefully it's done right every time.

Start off with Ruth's Jumbo Chop Salad (ask to split for two) dig into a Petite Filet (Trust me - it's a lot of food) and grab a side of the Au Gratin potatoes.  You can thank me later.  Don't forget to tip accordingly - although you're paying for a hefty meal, you should be provide with stellar service to boot.

Hard to find place in dining area without a reservation. But the best thing is they always find a table for you in the bar area of which the ambiance is lovely. Fillet steak surf & turf is highly recommended. Skinny chips are too skinny and way to small pieces.

The location has the ambiance of a 1970's steak house, very dark with an almost old bank feel to it.  But for what appears to be a nice place to eat the service and food here was sub par. We waited forever to get anything to drink after being seated. We ordered our full meal (salad, soup and mains) with the special request to get salad first and then waited 20 minutes for them to end up bringing the soup and salad at the same time. The side portions while generous their preparation are nothing special. If you're looking for a good steak I would stick with Alexander's.
By far the BEST steak I have ever had. They have consistently great food her and impeccable service. Prepare to splurge and spend a lot.
I always go here when I want the perfect steak- and the food is yummy! Very romantic chill atmosphere. Classy.

adr_address: Hotel Metropolis, 25 Mason St, San Francisco, CA 94102-2805, USA
formatted_address: Hotel Metropolis, 25 Mason St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
name: farmerbrown

reviews.text: Great atmosphere and excellent service. Portion sizes are small compared to other restaurants I’ve visited in San Francisco. I had the BBQ ribs. The sauce was delicious, the ribs themselves were a little tough and not really seasoned. My friends had the catfish platter and chicken and waffles. Both said the dishes were delicious. The blueberry lemonade is excellent.

Excellent dinner experience. Comfortable atmosphere, really nice staff. I had the endive salad with blood oranges, shells n' cheese, angel biscuits with fresh preserves, a large cucumber gimlet in a jar, and iced tea! Yeah, even for a vegetarian, this place nailed it. I'd go back.

When we arrived tonight, we had forgotten that we ate here years ago, and it was not memorable, so we weren't as excited. Tonight, farmerbrown redeemed itself. EVERYTHING that we ordered was flavorful, and the service was superb (thanks to Matthew)! We ate fried okra for an appetizer. It actually had pieces of fish. They were fried with cornmeal- it makes a big difference. Our party ordered the shrimp and grits (just a little salty), chicken and waffles, fried chicken with hamhock greens (deliciously spicy) and shells and cheese (perfect amount of cheese), and fried cornmeal catfish with cheesy grits (awesome grits!). We ended the evening with chocolate chip bread pudding with vanilla ice cream- so good. We will definitely return. The neighborhood is sketchy. It's cheaper to park in the garage before the restaurant ($15) vs turning the corner and parking in the next garage ($20).

Mmmm... Was a good birthday dinner!
We naturally ordered too much food. I had the pulled pork sandwich... it was worth it.

I recommend it to anyone who wants their arteries clogged in a tasty kind of way. I was very impressed, and don't feel I need to go back.

The prices aren't cheap, and the portions are small, but the service, food, and cocktails are outstanding!

If you go for dinner, I would recommend giving their Chicken & Waffles a shot. I was expecting something sweet, but was impressed by how savory the meal was. The chicken was perfectly cooked and was well complimented by the homemade Belgium waffle. 

If you're over 21 years of age and enjoy whiskey cocktails, I would suggest trying the Old-Soul Fashioned ... you won't be disappointed.  If you're not a whiskey fan, then I'd recommend the Farmhouse Lemonade.

vicinity: Hotel Metropolis, 25 Mason Street, San Francisco

adr_address: Ferry Building, 1 Ferry Building #3, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
formatted_address: Ferry Building, 1 Ferry Building #3, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
name: The Slanted Door

reviews.text:
I visited The Slanted Door during a recent work trip, and I was very impressed! 
I was very excited to see that they offer a good selection of non-alcoholic specialty drinks. I ordered a pineapple spritzer, which even looked pretty when it came out! It was the perfect mixture of pineapple, fizz, and mint.
The shaking beef was also delicious, with flavorful tender beef and delicious lime sauce on the side. But, the real star of the meal was the vanilla bean cheesecake: decadent vanilla bean cheesecake with a tart blood orange sauce, fresh blood orange slices and sweet honeycomb. I seriously considered going back every day I was in San Francisco just to get another piece of that cheesecake. 
I do feel that this place is a bit overpriced. However, you can tell that the food is fresh and care is put into the presentation, which I feel makes it worth it.

I came all the way from Australia to visit the bar at The Slanted Door, as it was highly recommended, and I was not disappointed! The staff are friendly and professional, and the cocktails are spot on--I should know, being in the industry myself. The food is also sublime. This place does hospitality to a T, and I guarantee you will have a great time if you visit The Slanted Door, regardless of whether you're a local or a tourist. I will definitely be back the next time I'm in town. Thanks again!
Exceptional Vietnamese food, great location.  The service was good.  Dishes were modern twists on some classics.  Would definitely consider revisiting this place next time I am in San Francisco.

My wife and I love this place and we have been there a few times over the last few years, most recently on NY eve last week. The food is absolutely outstanding, though not cheap. The chef melds Asian and American flavors into something pretty unique, and the execution is flawless. The ambience and service have also been consistently excellent. 

I would normally give them a 5-star review but the wine list holds me back, as it is pretty weak both in terms of the selection available and the quality of the wine served. This is less true when you buy a bottle but the selection is still incredibly biased toward German/Austrian wines...I don’t remember seeing so many Rieslings on a wine list at any other restaurant, outside of Germany perhaps. This really needs to be addressed if they want my fifth star.

The best "modern" Vietnamese I've had. It's expensive, but utterly delicious, with good cocktails as well. This sprawling restaurant is located at the northern corner of the Ferry Building, and for San Fran is extremely spacious. There's also outdoor seating and a takeout window on the inside hallway.

Between us, we had four shrimp, chicken, and vegetarian dishes (they are served "family style") and all were superlative-- intense flavors, crisp textures, balanced seasoning. The dishes are the appropriate size to share among 1-3 people, depending on appetite.

Two rounds of cocktails were equally tasty including my orange Caipirinha. Service was brisk, polite, and efficient.

It's pricey, especially if you are expecting Vietnamese to be a "cheap" cuisine (Asian cuisines as a whole get that bad rap), but then again this is waterfront in San Fran-- pricing is as expected considering that location.

vicinity: Ferry Building, 1 Ferry Building #3, San Francisco

adr_address: 865 Market St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
formatted_address: 865 Market St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Bazille

reviews.text: Nice restaurant located on the top floor of the Westfield Mall. Great views over downtown San Francisco, and a meal for two came out to less than $45. Highly recommended!

We went to lunch here on a Sunday during a birthday shopping outing. We've been here a few times.  The food was good, especially the wild salmon and club sandwich. The calamari appetizer was tasty. Staff was friendly and didn't rush us through our meal. Better than average store fare. We'll be back. Reservations suggested.

We regularly eat lunch before the theater. Service is gracious, city street view always interesting. We get favorites like Cilantro Shrimp salad and excellent soup. Quality of the food is consistent, spices enjoyable, there is a full bar for enhancements.
Great secret spot on the fourth floor of Nordstrom. Well-prepared, fresh food and great views. A hidden gem!
Great Fresh Fig and Berry salad! Also good choice of wine.

adr_address: 500 Brannan St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
formatted_address: 500 Brannan St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
name: Marlowe

reviews.text: Delicious upscale restaurant. Great service, they were very attentive. We ordered the raw ousters, baked oysters, brussel sprouts, duck liver, and bone marrow off the small plates menu. Everything was divine! We also had the steak which was great. A little pricey but worth it for how great everything was.

My fiancee and I love this place. We sat outside and dined on some delicious burgers and refreshing Mexican coca cola. We also enjoyed some donuts for desert! It was a great time and beautiful restaurant. Get there early though it's very well known in SF.

Marlowe is a good casual dining spot. We went here with a group of six ladies for a birthday celebration. It was my third time coming here and the stars of the night were the little gem salad, side of fries, and the burger. the cod main entree was hearty for a fish, but didn’t enjoy the texture as much. the stuffed peppers that came with the cod was actually the more tasty thing on the plate. we also ordered the oysters, which were delicious but noticed two of the oysters barely had the fresh water sitting in the shell. maybe it got spilled over? or they shucked it incorrectly - i’m not sure. found part of a shell in one of my oysters, but it was still good. overall, the dinner was good - but not crazy amazing.
This is such a feel good place. The decor is Americana and the food is exceptional. The mushroom polenta has such complex flavor and their cocktails are fantastic, I'm partial to the Baker's Wife.
Probably one of the best burgers I've had here in San Francisco. Great staff and really fun decor. Highly recommend checking this place out.

adr_address: 558 Sacramento St, San Francisco, CA 94111-3034, USA
formatted_address: 558 Sacramento St, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
name: Wayfare Tavern

reviews.text: Visited Wayfare Tavern after work for dinner. While we had a reservation, our entire party was not there on time so we had to wait a bit longer, but were seated immediately after our entire party was present. We were seated upstairs which was fairly quite until more customers were seated. There was a large private room for larger parties that seemed quite nice. The wait staff was very helpful, friendly, and prompt for table service. The food was delicious and would certainly recommend the fried chicken, hamburger, and deviled eggs. Additionally the salad dressing was surprisingly delicious. The main entree did take longer than expected, but was not that noticable as we were conversing; that said the waiter did apologize and noted that the operations manager may have mixed up the order, and was kind enough to provide us with dessert on the house. Overall, we were very impressed with the entire experience and would certainly visit again in the future.

They are known for the fried chicken. It was good, but I didn't think it was the best fried chicken I ever had.  Their whipped potatoes was delicious, just way too watery and didn't come with a spoon.  Over all, the food was tasty, but not something I would suggest to a friend since there are so many other places around.  The table service can be improved a little.  The hostess was very nice and kept me posted with the availability of the table even for the short wait we had.

We were so happy to find this restaurant. The food was amazing, presentation was wonderful and the service was top notch. We never waited for service.  We had the fried chicken - the best we've had, macaroni and cheese, whipped potatoes, devilled eggs and finished with a brownie sundae and we loved every bite! Wish we lived close enough to come back more often. It was the only restaurant we actually enjoyed while we were visiting SFO.

Great food, amazing service, and hands down the best whisky sour I've ever had. Get the fried chicken. Or the burger. Or the steak. Honestly, get anything. I've never been unsatisfied with my mail here.

This restaurant was very flexible when our plans all fell apart. We had a really nice dinner of their signature fried chicken  and tavern burger.  The burger was cooked perfectly, but my chicken was a little salty but good. 
And their deviled eggs were really good.  Also, don't forget to keep asking for more of their signature popovers, yum.

adr_address: 401 Taylor St, San Francisco, CA 94102-1701, USA
formatted_address: 401 Taylor St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
name: Jasper's Corner Tap and Kitchen

reviews.text:
Japsers serves really great food. I've loved everything I've tried on the menu and I'm sure I would have loved the item that they were no longer serving but was still listed on their menu. It's got a nice atmosphere and is not too far a walk from either of the shows we saw the couple of times I've been. 

Food aside, service was not great either time. To be fair, both times I've been were early enough that it wasn't crowded, but they had plenty of staff around, the service was just very slow. You'd think with fewer customers, they would be able to fix that. I will say that the food comes out right away, but flagging down someone to take our food order and then to bring us our check was difficult. 

Overall, a nice place with tasty offerings. Just expect to be there a while. We still made it to both of our shows on time though!

Typical fare and good for larger groups. Beer does toon is fine but nothing special. Service is good and friendly. Do it if you need a quick spot and are nearby. Don’t have insane expectations or you will be disappointed. But straight forward and reliable is what you will get here.

Super good ginger cocktails. Their Angus sliders and tater tots are not normal and are super great w ginger cocktails.  Their shrimp and grits is super savory and divine as an ending. Service is smiles and quick. Get your hedonist side out here.

My wife and I had breakfast there. Staff were attentive and courteous.  Breakfast was great. Open floor plan and natural lighting adds for a nice atmosphere.  The big plus was that the music was mostly 70's top 40 and the volume was subdued.

Went here for brunch and had really good food and a really good housemade Bloody Mary. If you're staying in this part of town it's a great place to eat at, I wouldn't go out of my way to make a special trip here other than that though.

adr_address: 450 Post St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
formatted_address: 450 Post St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
name: Farallon

reviews.text: I had a truly amazing experience at Farallon. I went with the chef's selection and had a spectacular seven course meal over a well-paced 3 hours. I really enjoyed my booth seat and view of the kitchen. It's clear that the head chef (who's been there for three years) knows his trade and he has built a high performing team. Thanks for the great meal and experience. I'd definitely recommend.

My wife was looking for a romantic dinner after we were able to get someone to watch the kids. The wait staff is exemplary and the happy hour menu was fantastic. The oysters were incredible (fresh shucked for the win), the ceviche was out of this world, and I seem to have run out of exemplars to describe the drinks and dessert. 
The prices while high are reflected in the quality of the food, wonderful ambience, and stupendous manners and service of the weight staff. It is worth the price if you can swing it.

We had a perfectly fabulous evening on March 2nd.! I’ll It is rare to find a restaurant that has such professional, knowledgeable and engaging staff. We ordered mixed drinks as well as wine, all excellent. Oysters were very fresh and perfectly presented. I loved my trout and my husband could hardly share a bite of his short ribs! Our friend got the steak which was perfectly cooked but if I ever order it , I will ask for less salt. The bread pudding dessert was a big hit!  The decor and general ambiance at Farallon is full of grace, and it offers a rare opportunity to have a private conversation in a public place. Before we left, our waiter told us about their amazing happy hour menu. We certainly will have to come back often!

The host was pleasant, he did a good job of noting reservations and greeted people as they walked in. The bone marrow was delicious, the halibut was buttery, tender and fresh. The berry margaritas on the rocks was so tasteful. The only complaint, our server was very rude. I already felt out of place dining at this fancy restaurant but felt even more out of place due to our servers' treatment. She was polite to every other table but not to mine.

Loved the atmosphere and surroundings, like the set of Jules Verne. Had the Tuna to start and the Swordfish as main, both excellent. FDNY cocktail was alright, didn't live up to the hype of being listed as the top cocktail on the menu, but maybe it would have been better on a cold SF day. Would definitely go again, and bring friends

adr_address: 400 Oyster Point Blvd # 131, South San Francisco, CA 94080-1997, USA
formatted_address: 400 Oyster Point Blvd # 131, South San Francisco, CA 94080, USA
name: Pointe Cafe

reviews.text: Very reasonable price and friendly staff
For being an office cafe/restaurant the food is actually really good. Thursday specials are the best. Thai chicken bowl with sweet curry.
Very clean and courteous staff
The quality of food was great for the price.  Service was quick.  There can be long lines at lunch so be sure to come early or call ahead.
Nice place for lunch in this area. But they have limited options

vicinity: 400 Oyster Point Boulevard # 131, South San Francisco

adr_address: 1300 Battery St, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
formatted_address: 1300 Battery St, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
name: Fog City

reviews.text: Very limited menu.  The butternut squash soup was very good but that was it.  Onion rings were cold, beef brisket was more of a fatty pot roast drowned in a sour BBQ sauce, served cold, the pizza my wife ordered was tasteless, and likewise cold.  Service was friendly but very, very slow.  Long delay between seating and ordering, and again between the soup/salads and entree arrival.  By the time the dessert menu arrived, we just wanted out of there.  Our daughter mentioned she passed a table as we were leaving where she overheard a couple discussing sending their brownie dessert back. Now it's six hours later and I woke up with acid reflux and a sick feeling.  Bottom line: while highly recommended by friends who live here, they had not been in years.  Wanted to like this far more than we did.  Disappointing.
It's a long time since I have been here and I'm still impressed. Good value for the money. Tasty food and friendly efficient service. No problem finding parking

During lunch hour, we were seated promptly, and our orders were served quickly.  The food was fresh and hot, but the service after that was extremely slow.  The remodeled dining area is nice, but was too loud when packed with the lunch crowd.
Very rude staff especially the manager.  Very unprofessional and full of attitude. Overpriced mediocre food and drinks although the drinks were good.  Would not recommend.
Good food. Great for small private parties. (20 ish people)

adr_address: 1326 9th Ave, San Francisco, CA 94122-2309, USA
formatted_address: 1326 9th Ave, San Francisco, CA 94122, USA
name: Social Kitchen & Brewery

reviews.text:
Beware: the online menu is not accurate in terms of price or availability. Actual prices are about 25% higher than listed.

Other than that I love this place. It has tons of seating, great service, and yummy food and beer at fairly standard SF prices. The food definitely leans more towards bar food, but it's still delicious. They tend to be out of the veggie (falafel) burgers, and the only other remotely healthy option is salad. 

If they'd just update the online menu on Google and keep veggie burgers in stock I'd happily give them 5 stars.

LOVED EVERYTHING ABOUT THE EXPERIENCE! 

First time here! Excellent customer service! Easy to take a reservation online! The food was good, despite how demanding I was with all the ingredients and sauces due to allergies! The chicken sandwich with dark meat was so delicious! The server even told us they were running behind due to lack of chefs in the kitchen! 

I was a bit surprised how small the menu was though! They did have vegan options! 

Now, the atmosphere was fantastic! It’s a combination of a bar, sports bar, brewery, a chic 20/30’s hang out spot, quite busy for a Thursday night, plenty of seating available, and just a fun space to be in! Totally recommend this spot for anyone who’s trying new places in the city! 

Totally will go again!

If you enjoy a complex and delicious beer, or a simple refined one, Social Kitchen is the spot. I had an amazing somewhat sour beer called Colliding Neutron Stars there last night. The menu description is a bit daunting but once it washes over your pallet you won't be confused. It's just great. I also had a really tasty colab beer called Proud Poppa that was a whole different animal but equally as satisfying. And the food? Also five stars. Thanks for dinner. I'll be back.
I had the best beer I had all week here. Lunar flip. Get one. The fries weren't amazing, but the beer made it up.

The beer has yet to disappoint and is always fresh. The food is reasonably priced and has some traditional comfort food. It has a large bar and some cool, two level seating. Only two TVs if I'm not mistaken so not the best place to go to watch a game. More of a sit and drink and/or eat type of place.

adr_address: Pier 43 1/2, Fisherman's Wharf, San Francisco, CA 94133, USA
formatted_address: Pier 43 1/2, Fisherman's Wharf, San Francisco, CA 94133, USA
name: Franciscan Crab Restaurant

reviews.text:
My son's allergies to shellfish recently withdrew, and he was excited to try seafood (especially crab) while we visited the city.  We stopped by The Franciscan down by the touristy Fisherman's Wharf / Embarcadero after searching reviews from several websites for several restaurants in the area.

EVERYTHING WAS PERFECT.

We visited around 1:30 on a Saturday, without a reservation, in a party of six, including three children.  It's a little pricey for us, more than our normal restaurant bills by a wide margin, so for us it represented a special occasion event.  

The waiter was the epitome of professional.  I'm sorry that I forget his name, but he was a middle-aged man with a neatly trimmed beard, working the east (bar) side of the restaurant.  He balanced attentiveness with giving us our space.

Bread and drinks were brought quickly, and they were delicious.  Entrees were well-timed, arriving about a little later. 

I fully recommend.

The restaurant has this '50s vibe and a nice view over the harbor. We ordered the super combo and it was filling for 3 people. The mussels and shrimp were nicely flavored in a garlic butter sauce. The crab was a bit dry for our taste. We were looking for somewhere to sit down and eat so this place satisfied our needs (compared to the stalls down the street, cheaper but no comfortable seating).

Great place! Servers are all very professional and helpful. Perfect view of the Bay from anywhere in the restaurant. The crab and shrimp platter was so delicious, we came back the following day for a second helping. Definitely recommend!

This is a "locals" place with views, food and service you dream about! End of Taylor, huge parking lot, prices extremely normal range, I take everyone there! It's March, in 3 months you couldn't pay me to go to Fisherman's Wharf, right now for a 6pm res, we found street parking, streets were empty, total enjoyable wharf experience. Great Prix Fixe $40 choice with House made Orgasmic Vanilla ice cream! Go, you'll go back!

Great service! I ordered the crab and it was buttery and delicious. The louis salad was also fresh and had a ton of crab and shrimp. If you get there early enough they will seat you at one of the ocean view tables which is quite nice. Most tables come with binoculars for you to look out at the ocean and Alcatraz.

adr_address: 560 Divisadero St, San Francisco, CA 94117-2213, USA
formatted_address: 560 Divisadero St, San Francisco, CA 94117, USA
name: Nopa

reviews.text:
Very nice cozy place. Good for a dinner with friends or business. It's my third time here. Very nice menu. If I have to make remark not to give them 5 stars is that the wine list can be better and also the beer selection.
Is a little crowded, bit of you have to wait a bit it's worthy the wait

Waited 30 minutes and got a seat at the communal table, it's first come first serve.  

I wanted some non-alcoholic drinks but they don't have a menu for that.  When I asked the waitress, she listed out some basic drinks like ginger beer and lemonades.  Later, I saw a lot of coffee and Samovar tea options on the dessert menu.  I don't understand why they didn't just give me that in the first place when I asked for non-alcoholic options.

My group ordered 2 appetizers: smelt, and brisket.  The smelt are just battered fried fish, nothing special, briskets are a bit salty for me (I only like the accompanied sauerkraut).  I got the seafood stew (cod & clams).  The stew came with a giant dollop of horseradish cream that burns, they should have put the horseradish on a separate container.  The fish was pretty salty and the horseradish was too pungent and kinda ruined the whole dish.   

Nope is a bust for me.  For the same price, I would rather go to Rich Table and have something tasty and unique.

This SF staple continues to impress. My first time for brunch didn't disappoint and included some of the best French toast I've ever had (and very rich with the custard soak). Get a reservation up to a month in advance. Dinner and cocktails are great too.

This is a place with a big reputation and I have to say it stood up to our expectations. Personally I found the food a bit too rich. A lot happens in your plate with many flavours at once. But I have to confess that despite that we really enjoyed it. Definitely we now understand why it's almost impossible to get in.

Incredible breakfast, hard to come up with faults. I love cooking breakfast at home but rarely go out to eat for it, we ended up in SF just about the right time and came to Nopa to start the day off right. Coffee was perfect and all 4 of our unique dishes were equally enjoyed. I will say despite the ratings that the burger isn't the best in the bay despite it being good and you should look elsewhere if you want a burger. One crazy thing is that I dropped my napkin accidentally and had a new one handed to me by the time I bent down to pick it up. That's some serious Michelin Star Rated service!
