formatted_address: 1970 Broadway, Lower Level, BART Station, Oakland, CA 94612, USA
name: SUBWAY®Restaurants

reviews.text: Very convenient location for commuters and BART employees, but is very difficult to locate without assistance.  Owner of this location chose to stop allowing orders via the Subway app - a key timesaving option. But the staff is great and so is the food.
Had the best service today. This subway still had yhe Rubens

I've been on a bit of a lucky streak with dates who "get it" when it comes to food. What a refreshing change for once! I shared my passionate opinion on SF Asian food over a glass of wine and he shared his experience with French and Moroccan food. During the conversation (where he also poked fun at my pronunciation of "Michelin"), Chez Maman came up and since it's a place I've had bookmarked for longer than I can remember, I jumped on the opportunity to try it out.
Small location which is essentially part of the train station.  Limited menu does not have the nationally advertised items.  Not very appealing in looks.  Staff tries their best, but..
Subway sandwiches are crap and this place no different.  How can people eat such generic and practically pre-manufactured garbage?

vicinity: 1970 Broadway, Lower Level, BART Station, Oakland

adr_address: 100 Spinnaker Dr, Sausalito, CA 94965-2181, USA
formatted_address: 100 Spinnaker Dr, Sausalito, CA 94965, USA
name: The Spinnaker

reviews.text:
We were barely in the door when the manager and bartender both greeted us and made us feel very welcome, a huge difference from a place up the road that made us feel just the opposite. Chris, the bartender, was fantastic engaging, and put up with our questions about what he liked on the menu then delivered two perfect mojitos. Gavin, the manager, was every bit as gracious and professional. All of this before we even got to the food... More later!

Following up from home, the food was excellent and the service continued to be stellar.

Great restaurant with a very nice views over the bay and the skyline of San Francisco. 
The staff is very organized and friendly. While you wait for a dinner table, you can order some appetizers or drinks on the bar zone. They will then call your name over the microphone.
You should definitely have some sea food  there.

Try to go at least once a year. The drive across the Golden Gate bridge, the ride through Sausalito, and the view of the bay and downtown SF is spectacular. Seems like the weather is always good. The food is even good, especially the clam chowder.

Terrific views. That's the main selling point and it works. Make sure you go on a sunny day. These are among the best views of San Francisco from Sausalito, if not the best. The food is good but comes at a price. The only issue was with our waiter, who was not friendly at all and was even a bit rude. Nonetheless I recommend this restaurant to anyone who wants to have a good time and see the views.
Beautiful setting.... amazing ambiance...delicious food. Breathtakingly beautiful at night. Totally worth every penny.

adr_address: 356 Kearny St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
formatted_address: 356 Kearny St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
name: Ramen Underground

reviews.text: One of my favorite ramen place in the city. Rich delicious broth, fresh egg noodles with perfectly cooked pork belly! Worth the wait!
Tonkatsu had great flavor. Not overpowering and the noodles were done very well with quality consistency. Very tasty. Great for a quick yet high quality bite.

Overall, I'm not sure this place is worth a second trip. The food isn't bad by any means, but the restaurant definitely gets crowded and busy, so expect a wait if you go anywhere near lunch time. Additionally for the price, the food just isn't worth it. Feeding just myself with a just middle of the road ramen and water, ended costing just under $15, which granted there is a $.35 card charge on there you should be aware of (oh and the $13 minimum per person and $12 per card (max 2) minimum). Not a bad meal, but not worth its scratch. There are better, less crowded options very near by
You have to try the ramen in this place, it is very good. Suggest get there before 11.30, otherwise you will have to order take away. Great price, and great food, great service!
Really good ramen.  There's more seating here than their old location across the street. Not great for large groups. Trying coming during an off hour.

adr_address: 360 Jessie St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
formatted_address: 360 Jessie St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: The Cavalier

reviews.text:
A nice sanctuary for breakfast. Well-lit, high ceilings, interesting art and decoration. My server was impossibly nice, and sincerely so. Definitely not cheap. And I agree with my fellow reviewer that the breakfast menu is quite small.  But it amply did the job for me. If you’re not ready to pay $6 for a side of avocado this will not be the place for you. But if you want a calm friendly place to linger over brunch (and aren’t on a tight budget), give it a try. 

Note: entrance on Jesse street (non-hotel side) is easy to miss. Look for red awning.

I love this place. The food is fantastic for both dinner and breakfast. Although the breakfast menu is quite small. I have not had the pleasure of tasting the brunch menu yet but I looking forward to it! I highly recommend this place for delicious and hearty upscale dinning. The price is a little high compared to everyday food but it is well worth it.

We went to the Cavalier last night for Valentine's Day.  5:30 seating.  I have to say, they treated us like queen and king.  We got a great table and excellent service for the entire evening.  Valentines's Day has a 4 course fixed price service, with wine pairings as an option.  My husband had the steak and I had the duck breast.  The vegetables were wonderful.  The wine pairing was fantastic.   But really, it was the service that made the evening so special.  I can't wait to return and bring friends with us.

Consistently delicious healthy food and excellent service. I’ve been a few times when traveling for work and although on the higher price end, it’s always provided a comfortable homely atmosphere. Great to get some vegetables when traveling and I had the cod with Brussel sprout chips this time.
Ambience is that of classy every day couple to business team outings. Traditional English food with a clean sharp presentation. Fair menu selection. Large wine list. Great for a date night.

adr_address: One Ferry Building, #11, San Francisco, CA 94111-4228, USA
formatted_address: One Ferry Building, #11, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
name: Hog Island Oyster Co.

reviews.text: My husband took me here for my birthday. We had a blast! Food was perfect, seafood cannot be any fresher. Service was fast, staff were nice. We were here on a Monday night so it was not as packed. It is a bit pricey but I wouldn't say it is overkill. I wanna come back and try their Brunch.

Great service with great food. Although I’m not a big fan of seafood, this place definitely convinced me that I should be. Got the grilled oysters, clam chowder, and the sliders. The food was so good that I only got one picture of all the things.

Would recommend that you come early or make a reservation. Is a little on the pricier side.
great quality sea food. We had clam chowder and it was delicious. Everything smells and tastes fresh and the place is really clean! Go there on a sunny day and enjoy the views!

Service is impeccable. We got our oysters before our drinks and weren’t even mad about it (because we were there for the oysters mainly), but before we knew it our server had sent out a “gift” from the kitchen to make up for it. The flavors were great. Coincidentally our least favorite oysters were the Hog Island namesake. But our favorites were the ones recommended by our server, so I would definitely trust a recommendation here! Also our “gift” was grilled oysters and we never try any cooked oyster - I am so happy he sent these out since I never would have known how delicious. Do yourself a favor and try the garlic and the chipotle grilled oysters.

Great quality. Oysters were obviously delicious, but the other items on their menu are great as well. My husband and I always makes this one of our date night spots and we always bring friends and family who are visiting here. Highly recommend!
